In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims April 2016 as National Financial Capability Month. The President emphasizes the importance of providing individuals with the knowledge and resources to make informed decisions about their finances. He highlights the need for reliable information and tools to protect and empower individuals, particularly during important life events such as buying a home, pursuing education, or saving for retirement. The President encourages Americans to access free and reliable financial information through resources such as the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau and various websites. He also discusses efforts to educate young people about the dangers of excessive debt and the importance of financial management skills. The article concludes with a call to preserve the belief in rewarding hard work and providing equal opportunity for all.